description:
The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the S&P China 500 Index.
 Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index selects the largest 500 eligible companies from the broader S&P Total China BMI Index. The fund is non-diversified.
